.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-9-5::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: coffee, fanta, sprite, water
There 4 different types of food: pumpkin, tomato, cucumber, onion
The people use 4 different means of transport: train, jet-ski, tram, bus
 1. the person driving the tram is not to the right of the person drinking water##8
 2. the person eating pumpkin and the person drinking fanta have different parity positions##9
 3. the person driving the bus is the person drinking sprite##1
 4. the person drinking coffee is not to the right of the person driving the jet-ski##8
 5. the person drinking sprite is somewhere to the left of the person drinking coffee##5
 6. the person drinking coffee and the person eating cucumber have different parity positions##9
 7. the person drinking fanta is somewhere to the left of the person eating tomato##5
 8. the person driving the tram is on the left of the person drinking fanta##1
 9. the person eating pumpkin and the person drinking water have the same parity positions##9
10. the person driving the bus is on the far left or far right##3
11. the person eating onion is on the left or right of the person driving the train##3

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1     |       2       |     3      |     4      |
| Beverage    | sprite | coffee | fanta      | water        |
| Food        | cucumber  | pumpkin       | onion     | tomato  |
| Transport   | bus      | tram        | jet-ski | train |

